The paper discusses a processing scheme for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) targeted at embedded applications with limited memory budgets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to processing CNNs that is designed to reduce memory requirements, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on embedded applications suggests that it may also be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
